The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Sunday, January 18, 2004 				 Uco Bank eyes growth
																								Madurai, Jan. 17 (PTI): Uco Bank plans to raise its volume of business to Rs 1 lakh crore by 2007 from the current Rs 52,000 crore, chairman and managing director V. P. Shetty said today.																								He said the bank was almost written off in 1999 after it suffered serious losses. But now it had climbed to the eighth position among the nationalised banks in the country in the volume of business. One can compare Uco Bank with any of the best banks in the country. Our vision is to make it a top-class bank in the country.																								The investors, who invested Rs 250 crore during the public issue, now see their investment doubled, he said. 
